cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning word embeddings, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new approach to learning word embeddings using k-way co-occurrences, which is a novel contribution to the field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a theoretical approach to prove a relationship between the joint probability of k words and the sum of l2 norms of their embeddings, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its approach on various NLP tasks, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
